      "source": [
        "import re\n",
        "\n",
        "def standardize_column_names(df):\n",
        "    new_columns = []\n",
        "    for col in df.columns:\n",
        "        # Convert to lowercase\n",
        "        new_col = col.lower()\n",
        "        # Replace specific characters like '#' with '_no'\n",
        "        if new_col == 's#':\n",
        "            new_col = 's_no'\n",
        "        # Replace spaces, parentheses, and other special characters with underscores\n",
        "        new_col = re.sub(r'\\s+|\\(|\\)|\\band\\b|\\bor\\b|\\bnot\\b|\\b--\\b|\\b/\\b', '_', new_col)\n",
        "        # Remove any remaining non-alphanumeric characters (except underscore)\n",
        "        new_col = re.sub(r'[^a-z0-9_]', '', new_col)\n",
        "        # Replace multiple underscores with a single underscore\n",
        "        new_col = re.sub(r'_{2,}', '_', new_col)\n",
        "        # Remove leading/trailing underscores\n",
        "        new_col = new_col.strip('_')\n",
        "        new_columns.append(new_col)\n",
        "    df.columns = new_columns\n",
        "    return df\n",
        "\n",
        "df = standardize_column_names(df)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Standardized column names:\")\n",
        "print(df.columns.tolist())\n"

Cela indique que le prix du pétrole n'est pas uniquement un coût de marché, mais aussi un outil de politique fiscale.\n",
